commit_message:
Remove SERVICE_TENANT variable in redstack

In the fix for using the admin tenant for performing flavor-create
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/155151), the variable SERVICE_TENANT
was left behind. Since it is no longer needed, it was removed.

Change-Id: I728b2b48d2eca82d359387f83f686646a38f5c6d
Closes-Bug: #1421463

commit_message:
Adds floatingip allocate,release integration tests

This submission is to add test_floating.py which tests allocate
floatingip and release floatingip methods. And to
allow this I have added floatingip.py with two methods
to allocate and release floatingip. Modified accesssecuritypage.py
which has _click_on_floatingip_link method and projectpage.py which
has go_to_floatingip_page method with _click_on_access_security_menu
method using NavigationBarRegion's object.

Partially implements blueprint: selenium-integration-testing

Change-Id: Ic09874c0e000aff62ae5ddfc809ff886ec3a7e05

After this patch If19be8579ca734a899cdd673c919eee8165aaa0e refactored

unimplemented by the HyperV security groups driver.

For this reason, binding ports fails with NotImplementedError if

Until the HyperV security groups driver reaches parity, the
use_enhanced_rpc property should be set to False on the

Closes-Bug: #1415523
'}]
commit_message:
Hyper-V: Fixes security groups issue

After this patch If19be8579ca734a899cdd673c919eee8165aaa0e refactored
securitygroups_rpc, prepare_devices_filter attempts to use methods
unimplemented by the HyperV security groups driver.

For this reason, binding ports fails with NotImplementedError if
security groups are enabled.

Until the HyperV security groups driver reaches parity, the
use_enhanced_rpc property should be set to False on the
HyperVSecurityAgent, falling back to the old behaviour.

Change-Id: I1a7ee2b92367d2d59932b8b39372a055bf19951b
Closes-Bug: #1415523

subject: Improve multilock class and its associated unit test
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-02-13 19:45:41.000000000', 'files': ['taskflow/utils/lock_utils.py', 'taskflow/tests/unit/test_utils.py', 'taskflow/tests/unit/test_utils_lock_utils.py', 'taskflow/utils/misc.py'], 'message': 'Improve multilock class and its associated unit test

In the multilock unit test check that all values were
acquired (as expected). Also use a class constant for
the number of threads to spin up when testing timing
overlaps and use the module constant for the duration
to wait (to try to trigger overlaps) and use a new helper
utility function to make it more obvious what is happening
in the multilock release method.

Also swaps out the usage of time.time in the lock utils
unit test to attempt to use monotonic time (when it can
be used) so that false positives are unable to happen (using
time.time it is possible for time to go backwards and cause
a non-existent overlap to appear).

Change-Id: Ifb3967e1c1da41e1b7ac0793fc6a99f84de2a907
'}]
commit_message:
Improve multilock class and its associated unit test

In the multilock unit test check that all values were
acquired (as expected). Also use a class constant for
the number of threads to spin up when testing timing
overlaps and use the module constant for the duration
to wait (to try to trigger overlaps) and use a new helper
utility function to make it more obvious what is happening
in the multilock release method.

Also swaps out the usage of time.time in the lock utils
unit test to attempt to use monotonic time (when it can
be used) so that false positives are unable to happen (using
time.time it is possible for time to go backwards and cause
a non-existent overlap to appear).

Change-Id: Ifb3967e1c1da41e1b7ac0793fc6a99f84de2a907

commit_message:
Add support of nova network for share-networks API and DB

We need support of Nova network in API and DB first, before addon of support
of it for drivers.

Changes:
- Extend ShareNetwork model with column 'nova_net_id'
- Add migration with addon of column 'nova_net_id' to ShareNetwork model
- Add support of new key 'nova_net_id' to the API of share networks
- Make it mutually exclusive with Neutron network data

Implements nova-network-api-support
Change-Id: I1b04a74aec6aed1b9bbf6e4deebee726bd0830c2

commit_message:
Add run_as_root option to utils.execute

This change adds the run_as_root option that exists in the
processutils.execute method. This option makes it possible
to just look up the root_helper from the config when
necessary, while still making it possible to not use any
privilege escalation.

Currently, processutils.execute exposes some eventlet issues
in the neutron codebase, otherwise this patch would just move
us over to using it.

Change-Id: Ic9ebe77dada4f7f044f009ff04494906d4f50ae2
Partially-Implements: blueprint rootwrap-daemon-mode

commit_message:
Make listing of networks compatible for neutron and nova in devstack

We have possibility to setup service instances for Generic driver within
devstack plugin. It requires network ID, that is taken by network name.
Now used Neutron API to get this information, Nova API allows it too.
So, make it compatible for both, that will be useful with upcoming support
of Nova network within Generic driver.

Change-Id: I902fd734e8e35c4db57916bd2701fc76e3a92932

commit_message:
Move definition of couple of config opts to proper module

Define config options 'osapi_max_limit' and 'osapi_share_base_URL' in proper
module to be able to run module "manila.api.common" without import of
module "manila.common.config". Without it all unit test modules that import
"manila.api.common" fail due to not defined mentioned config opts.

Change-Id: I725ab6cc7d777b3384bdd9095c72ecd65079e6cf
Closes-Bug: #1194315

agent used to cache the context that is used in
invoking RPCs to the plugin to notify the

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-02-17 18:41:20.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/tests/unit/db/test_l3_dvr_db.py', 'neutron/db/l3_dvr_db.py'], 'message': 'Fix FIP agent gw port delete based on external net

Today the FIP agent gateway port for DVR is deleted
based on the host. When there are multiple external
networks, then the port deletion for the second
external network may fail.

So the current fix checks for the valid host and
external network id and then deletes the FIP agent
gw port if it is the last one to be deleted.

Closes-Bug: #1421886

commit_message:
Fix FIP agent gw port delete based on external net

Today the FIP agent gateway port for DVR is deleted
based on the host. When there are multiple external
networks, then the port deletion for the second
external network may fail.

So the current fix checks for the valid host and
external network id and then deletes the FIP agent
gw port if it is the last one to be deleted.

Closes-Bug: #1421886

Change-Id: Ic5dfb88409c39d06d912263b338d0c5f7ebd3bcb

commit_message:
Tests: Remove TestWSGIService.test_reset_pool_size_to_default

This test invokes Cinder WSGIService.Service() and asserts
against values that are only manipulated in wsgi.Server(),
which WSGIService is based on.

We also have TestWSGIServer.test_reset_pool_size_to_default
which does the same thing for wsgi.Server().

Remove this test since it duplicates the TestWSGIServer test
and tests code which is an additional layer of abstraction
(cinder.WSGIService) away from the class that the code belongs
to (wsgi.Server).

Change-Id: I68d6f479da26e75618bfa773c84273501926ab07

commit_message:
Refactor how to remove compute nodes when service is deleted

service_id is about to be deprecated and won't be updated in a next patch.
We need instead to make sure that we can remove the nested compute nodes
by filtering on the host field.

Note: in order to get the host field value, we need to do an extra DB call
but we assume it as reasonable as it's only an admin action for a very
specific case (service deletion)

Partially-Implements: blueprint detach-service-from-computenode

Change-Id: Iaf03c45b23f2b3fd759f8e2a0deb92c0bea2a408

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-17 14:16:15.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/dell/dell_storagecenter_api.py'], 'message': 'Dell Storage Center: Add retries to API calls

In heavily loaded networks we have seen some cases
of temporary ConnectionErrors when making REST API
calls. There are usually successful calls just prior
and immediately after these failures, so it appears
to be a transient condition.

This patch utilizes the recently merged retry decorator
to add some retry handling to the REST API calls when
this condition is encountered.

With a test script looping through repeatedly running
CI against this first patch I was able to validate
that it addresses the issue. Out of 20 runs, a full

Closes-Bug: 1422742
Change-Id: I1279a7696068aee534498bb18f4f6b4fbb7a33d5
'}]
commit_message:
Dell Storage Center: Add retries to API calls

In heavily loaded networks we have seen some cases
of temporary ConnectionErrors when making REST API
calls. There are usually successful calls just prior
and immediately after these failures, so it appears
to be a transient condition.

This patch utilizes the recently merged retry decorator
to add some retry handling to the REST API calls when
this condition is encountered.

With a test script looping through repeatedly running
CI against this first patch I was able to validate
that it addresses the issue. Out of 20 runs, a full
2/3 of the tests passed showing that the retry was
used. These test runs would have failed without the
retry.

The output from these test runs can be viewed here:

http://oslogs.compellent.com/?C=N;O=D

Pertinent results are dell-sc-iscsi-1554792015-12*

Once merged we should be able to enable full third
party CI testing with some expectation of reliable
results.

Closes-Bug: 1422742
Change-Id: I1279a7696068aee534498bb18f4f6b4fbb7a33d5

commit_message:
API handler and API v1.1 Queue endpoints

This change adds the API handler module. This module will be the
connection between the transport and the API. The transport interacts
with this module by creating a Request and calling the process_request
function. The API, then, is in charge of processing that Request.
The API expects that the data in the request is already validated by
the transport.

In an effort to make this extensible, each API version has to define
it own endpoint module. This module interacts with the storage directly.

A Response will be returned to the transport.

In the following patches the rest of the endpoints will be added and
the validation of the Requests will be implemented.

Change-Id: I48b1937d7f5dec058879960bc556dee2a9c35b70
Partial-Implements: blueprint cross-transport-api-spec

commit_message:
Vendorpassthru doesn't get correct 'self'

This commit makes sure that all the {vendor, driver}_routes get
a different copy of the metadata dictionary and not a reference to
it. This fix a problem of objects getting the wrong reference to 'self'
when inheriting from the vendor interface.

Change-Id: Ia98c1d95db10b4387879771462fbf04faf4249da

commit_message:
define variables for Trove to be used in local.conf

This defines a number of variables for Trove configuration files
and options
In addition to general cleanup within devstack, this also enables 
consumers to enable features such as Openstack profiling, without
the need to repeat the hardcoding of these parameters in their
local.conf

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-02-17 21:28:24.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute_utils.py', 'nova/compute/utils.py'], 'message': "Expand try/except for get_machine_ips

Commit b838ca28e0ffda21b298a4514a647fc74c154f4a added get_machine_ips
and copied it from swift but didn't put the try/except in the same
scope, essentially swift commit 76afb46d91bb32dfcbda829408d6b0735526b92f.
This causes a ValueError failure race bug in resize tests in the gate.

This change simply expands the scope of the try/except like it is in
swift and adds a test to cover that.

Note that we should move this utility function into oslo at some point
if multiple projects are needing this.

Closes-Bug: #1422901

Change-Id: Iccceca4b9706ac7723563fbd2065f40586400527
"}]
commit_message:
Expand try/except for get_machine_ips

Commit b838ca28e0ffda21b298a4514a647fc74c154f4a added get_machine_ips
and copied it from swift but didn't put the try/except in the same
scope, essentially swift commit 76afb46d91bb32dfcbda829408d6b0735526b92f.
This causes a ValueError failure race bug in resize tests in the gate.

This change simply expands the scope of the try/except like it is in
swift and adds a test to cover that.

Note that we should move this utility function into oslo at some point
if multiple projects are needing this.

Closes-Bug: #1422901

Change-Id: Iccceca4b9706ac7723563fbd2065f40586400527

commit_message:
Update CI boxes

Update the CentOS 6 CI box from 6.4 to 6.5. This is needed to support
RDO which in turn is a requirement for the rgw/keystone CI tests.

Add CentOS 7 and Ubuntu 14.04 boxes so we can CI test them as a basis
to add support for them.

Because rspec-system and rspec-system-puppet are deprecated in favor
of beaker add dependencies on a fork to provide the necessary features.
This is temporary until all tests are switched to beaker.

Change-Id: I0ef014ff73a431a691fc25c35f6461fec614c337

subject: Add a list_all_sections method to ConfigOpts
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-05 10:59:26.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_config/tests/test_cfg.py', 'oslo_config/cfg.py'], 'message': "Add a list_all_sections method to ConfigOpts

Currently there is no way of getting the list of all sections defined
in the files, without accessing private parts of the library. This patch
adds a method that makes it possible.

Why do we need the list of all sections? Because we have separate
sections for the panels and dashboards, and it's impossible to tell
what panels and dashboards are available before reading the
configuration. Forcing the users to list all the sections in a separate
place is information duplication, error-prone and bad usability. So
the way we do it is listing all the sections, and then registering the
groups for the ones that we care about.

Change-Id: Id7b8f8bd2423123b4c3745d78fa857a5d94e02f0
"}]
commit_message:
Add a list_all_sections method to ConfigOpts

Currently there is no way of getting the list of all sections defined
in the files, without accessing private parts of the library. This patch
adds a method that makes it possible.

Why do we need the list of all sections? Because we have separate
sections for the panels and dashboards, and it's impossible to tell
what panels and dashboards are available before reading the
configuration. Forcing the users to list all the sections in a separate
place is information duplication, error-prone and bad usability. So
the way we do it is listing all the sections, and then registering the
groups for the ones that we care about.

Change-Id: Id7b8f8bd2423123b4c3745d78fa857a5d94e02f0

commit_message:
Support i18n messages in config generator

if opt.help is i18n'ed then we land up in trouble since
Message objects do not support addition and a TypeError
gets thrown. So we just use a better way to construct
the string to avoid the TypeError.

Closes-Bug: #1408032
Change-Id: If1feb65c6467f1c8176369f49d128c172c569c66

* remove old bug patches
* cleanup platform packages

* add user and group attributes

commit_message:
Fix for l2gateway agent not coming up on devstack

The patch set contains a fix for the problem
where the L2 gateway agent (manager.py) does
not get the host information in the conf file
thereby throwing an exception. Additionally,
it also fixes a problem where the manager.py
does not reraise the exception thereby causing
exceptions in the method
_connect_to_ovsdb_server().

Change-Id: I53348562301358e8f3f5a2e9af6ce1649134db4e

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-16 18:08:37.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': "Libvirt: Gracefully Handle Destroy Error For LXC

When libvirt destroys a container it will attempt to send a shutdown
to the init process, then kill all of the procceses left over. If
they don't die fast enough, libvirt will raise an error. The
container will eventually die in most cases. So, instead of erroring
the destroy, we should let the wait_for_destroy logic continue to
see if the instance goes away.

Change-Id: I1feb767e82bc77ad7ae63852a043d67844245626
Closes-Bug: #1413705
"}]
commit_message:
Libvirt: Gracefully Handle Destroy Error For LXC

When libvirt destroys a container it will attempt to send a shutdown
to the init process, then kill all of the procceses left over. If
they don't die fast enough, libvirt will raise an error. The
container will eventually die in most cases. So, instead of erroring
the destroy, we should let the wait_for_destroy logic continue to
see if the instance goes away.

Change-Id: I1feb767e82bc77ad7ae63852a043d67844245626
Closes-Bug: #1413705

commit_message:
Support SR-IOV mechanism driver in ML2

* Rename neutron::plugins::ml2::driver to
  neutron::plugins::ml2::type_driver to allow a namespace flexibility.
* Add neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver to follow type drivers
  configuration model.
* Add support to configure specific parameters for SR-IOV mechanism
  driver in adding parameters in both neutron::plugins::ml2 and
  neutron::plugins::ml2::mech_driver.
* Add a unit test with a new context when running SR-IOV mechanism
  driver.
* Configure SR-IOV parameters in standard ML2 configuration file to
  avoid packaging issue if neutron-server does not load ml2_conf_sriov.ini.
* Add neutron-sriov-nic-agent support with neutron::agents::ml2::sriov
* Add unit tests for neutron::agents::ml2::sriov

Source:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SR-IOV-Passthrough-For-Networking

Change-Id: I724e8bdf48619f00af2c198714f2e4a69f968cab
(cherry picked from commit d3a39eb89dc98c23b05d651e938e831de11fc1e5)

commit_message:
Add missing database updates for cluster events

Steps to reproduce issue:
1) Create cluster
2) Try to get cluster via client

Sometimes, received cluster would contains outdated info
about provision progress. This patch close this issue

Partially implements blueprint event-log

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-02-13 18:57:49.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/db/test_migrations.py', 'nova/tests/unit/objects/test_compute_node.py', 'nova/objects/service.py', 'nova/tests/unit/compute/test_resource_tracker.py', 'nova/tests/unit/compute/test_compute.py', 'nova/tests/unit/objects/test_objects.py', 'nova/db/sqlalchemy/migrate_repo/versions/277_add_compute_version_column.py', 'nova/db/sqlalchemy/models.py', 'nova/objects/compute_node.py', 'nova/tests/unit/api/openstack/compute/contrib/test_hosts.py', 'nova/tests/unit/compute/test_tracker.py', 'nova/tests/unit/compute/test_multiple_nodes.py', 'nova/compute/resource_tracker.py', 'nova/tests/unit/db/test_db_api.py'], 'message': "Add the 'version' column to the compute_nodes table.

WIP - do not merge until spec is approved.

When installations of OpenStack are upgraded, it is common to update
compute nodes individually instead of all at once. Some of the changes
that will be coming later in the patch series will require the scheduler
to be able to distinguish between older compute nodes and those updated
with at least the Kilo version of the code. During the mid-cycle, the
consensus was to add a column to the compute_nodes table that would be
populated by the compute node upon startup with its current software
version. Discussion on the spec for this settled on a string column that
would default to '0', but would be populated by the current RPC version
that the compute node supported. This way future updates to the compute

Change-Id: Ib12d7f739be1efbf344dc7f37ee2bbe774f8f92b

commit_message:
Add the 'version' column to the compute_nodes table.

WIP - do not merge until spec is approved.

When installations of OpenStack are upgraded, it is common to update
compute nodes individually instead of all at once. Some of the changes
that will be coming later in the patch series will require the scheduler
to be able to distinguish between older compute nodes and those updated
with at least the Kilo version of the code. During the mid-cycle, the
consensus was to add a column to the compute_nodes table that would be
populated by the compute node upon startup with its current software
version. Discussion on the spec for this settled on a string column that
would default to '0', but would be populated by the current RPC version
that the compute node supported. This way future updates to the compute
node software could require a higher minimum version for changes made in
order to be sure that the nodes would work correctly with it.

Change-Id: Ib12d7f739be1efbf344dc7f37ee2bbe774f8f92b

commit_message:
Change calls to service information for Hypervisors API

As we want to split how to access service information from the compute nodes,
let's provide a new way to get the services by getting all the services and
get the one from the compute host field

Partially-Implements: blueprint detach-service-from-computenode

Change-Id: If3f9e73eedd71b779fc6984c53eec0023e39549d

run_tests.sh

run_tests.sh
tools/colorizer.py
tools/install_venv.py
tools/install_venv_common.py
tools/install_venv_common.pyc

unit tests.

Add hooks for devstack testing

Add hooks for devstack testing.  Also add nose to test requirements to

commit_message:
Add concurrency decorator to repo factory functions

Since the get_*_repository functions are getting accessing global
variables (that are the repo classes), adding a locking mechanism for
those functions might be necessary when running in a multithreaded
environment. The same is already done in the crypto plugin code.

Change-Id: I03cd2ba11573785684ace9510265ce74b8c08b50

Patching time.sleep with 'None' is always the wrong
thing to do, because it removes the ability for the
thread scheduler to do anything useful, changes the
semantics of the system-under-test and may lead to
deadlocks. Patch with eventlet.sleep(0) instead.

commit_message:
Don't mock time.sleep with None

Patching time.sleep with 'None' is always the wrong
thing to do, because it removes the ability for the
thread scheduler to do anything useful, changes the
semantics of the system-under-test and may lead to
deadlocks. Patch with eventlet.sleep(0) instead.

See Dan Berrange's analysis in comment #2 at
https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1412742

Change-Id: Iad6cb63cb579bb9e0d8ef0c6e626c80053468157
related-bug: #1412742

commit_message:
Bump pycadf to 0.8.0

The newest pycadf library has content that keystone server plans
on leveraging. We need a newer version to be specified for kilo
because, with the juno version is capped, trying to access new
functions with the capped versions causes grenade to fail.

Change-Id: Ie2f7cda3fcb441f09f033561f10e8ffe712ea296

subject: Use canonical MySQL root pwd reset procedure
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-10 23:08:07.000000000', 'files': ['trove/guestagent/strategies/restore/mysql_impl.py'], 'message': "Use canonical MySQL root pwd reset procedure

Current Implementation:
Trove restores InnoDB backups by operating directly on the file system.
This means that the restored database would still use
the old (and potentially no longer available) root password.
Trove therefore needs to reset the password on the restored databases.
This was originally done by starting the service in the
safe mode (which allows root login without password) and
executing 'SET PASSWORD FOR ...' statement to reset the password.

Proposed Improved Solution:
The recommended generic procedure for resetting a 'forgotten' root
password is documented in the official MySQL doc:
http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.6/en/resetting-permissions.html

Added '--skip-grant-tables' to 'mysqld_safe' startup parameters.
That is required for unrestricted access to the user table.
The server can be instructed to start using grant tables at any
time by executing 'FLUSH PRIVILEGES' statement.
Added '--skip-networking' to prevent anybody from sneaking in
across the network while resetting the root password.
Replaced the password-reset statement with a direct user table update
followed by 'FLUSH PRIVILEGES'.
Removed '--protocol' parameter from the mysqladmin shutdown call,
as we started the database with '--skip-networking' and the guestagent
is running locally anyways.
We also check for errors in the password-reset stage,
so that a proper error message (including cause) can be logged.

Tested with MySQL  5.5/5.6 and Percona

Closes-Bug: 1419995
Change-Id: I86777c4177cb46d61573c564335b529d7a1da52a
"}]
commit_message:
Use canonical MySQL root pwd reset procedure

Current Implementation:
Trove restores InnoDB backups by operating directly on the file system.
This means that the restored database would still use
the old (and potentially no longer available) root password.
Trove therefore needs to reset the password on the restored databases.
This was originally done by starting the service in the
safe mode (which allows root login without password) and
executing 'SET PASSWORD FOR ...' statement to reset the password.

Proposed Improved Solution:
The recommended generic procedure for resetting a 'forgotten' root
password is documented in the official MySQL doc:
http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.6/en/resetting-permissions.html

Added '--skip-grant-tables' to 'mysqld_safe' startup parameters.
That is required for unrestricted access to the user table.
The server can be instructed to start using grant tables at any
time by executing 'FLUSH PRIVILEGES' statement.
Added '--skip-networking' to prevent anybody from sneaking in
across the network while resetting the root password.
Replaced the password-reset statement with a direct user table update
followed by 'FLUSH PRIVILEGES'.
Removed '--protocol' parameter from the mysqladmin shutdown call,
as we started the database with '--skip-networking' and the guestagent
is running locally anyways.
We also check for errors in the password-reset stage,
so that a proper error message (including cause) can be logged.

Tested with MySQL  5.5/5.6 and Percona

Closes-Bug: 1419995
Change-Id: I86777c4177cb46d61573c564335b529d7a1da52a

commit_message:
Delete qg device during DVR-SNAT router deletion

In the DVR SNAT case, the 'qg' device was not deleted because
of patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/151882/

During functional testing, the device is deleted
during the external bridge deletion. Because that happens after
the SNAT namespace is already deleted, it can cause a kernel
panic or ovs-vswitchd crash for certain OVS versions.

Also added assertions that all router interfaces were properly
cleaned up during functional testing, and enabled the unit tests
to catch this type of error.

Change-Id: Ica86a030860aa967d5b685b5bfb5546a85b2a809
Closes-Bug: #1418097

mimicking the way this new plugin interface should work.

Mixing apt-get installed packages and pip installed packages is an

commit_message:
Stop installing nova python dependencies packages from apt-get

Mixing apt-get installed packages and pip installed packages is an
absolute nightmare. For example:

The max version of suds in pip is 0.4.0, but ubuntu installs version
0.4.1 which isn't even out yet.

Unfortunately not every python package can be pip installed yet, so leave
a few.

Change-Id: I7268462bd784d9682f009eb1a821ca04fe161703

commit_message:
Change nodes so that they end in admin mac suffx instead of number

Previously the nodes would end in a number iterator to ensure they where
unique, however this makes working with the nodes generated this way
difficult as they are referred to as by their admin interface mac.

This changes it so the slave nodes will receive the suffix of the admin
mac.

Change-Id: I74743156c92cfeb9ec7a54f6cced65fd927ec2e7

commit_message:
Implements: blueprint heat-template

Previously, the kolla heat template was maintained outside of
the project in the larsks/heat-kubernetes repo. This patch adds
the templates to the project's devenv directory. Additionally,
the patch updates the templates and documentation to reflect
the design changes outlined in the following spec:

https://github.com/stackforge/kolla/blob/master/specs/containerize-openstack.rst

Change-Id: I11305f87cceb2495478d458a7e381d20838e664a

commit_message:
Bump openstackclient version min 1.0.2

Devstack now requires openstackclient>=1.0.2
(I2fdca28ae97a215cff5e2a6dd7cab2d3321caa6c), and we should make the
version required by devstack and global requirements align. That way we
can specify the version of openstackclient needed in devstack from
global-requirements. Making it the single source of truth for version
requirements.

Change-Id: Ibfb2234b06b5447adb028d1c93980f10e93dd830

commit_message:
Fix Datasource not found error for policy table commands

The code always check ds_id in get_items() and raise
exception if datasource not found. In policy table list/show,
only policy_id should be provided. E.g.
openstack congress policy table list classification
ERROR: openstack Datasource not found None (HTTP 400)
(Request-ID: req-3e1b2f4b-0808-44a1-b659-ccda0673f498)

Change-Id: I5c85475241065dab94962a4b5e9a040a5d395055

commit_message:
MySql cookbook ver 6 changes

mysql cookbook is now provider driven, and no longer has default
attributes, like server_root_password.
For the password, now always using the Common password methods.

For the other mysql attributes we used, these were moved into the
attributes mysql.rb file.

The attribute name space was changed from
[mysql][**attr**]  and [mysql][tunable][**attr**]  to
[openstack][mysql][**attr**]

This patch requires updates to the database and mysql-chef-gem cookbooks.mysql cookbook ver 6 changes

Change-Id: I05d27de80de0371503c5fa71591b4600bbeb2ca9
Implements: blueprint trusty-juno

commit_message:
Modified build-app build-lp unittest-app shell.py to use swift

We may use swift as the backend storage for custom language
packs and DUs. This patch adds that support.

For DUs, we also generate a tempURL which would be used to
download the DU on the VM and spin up the app as a container.

Closes-Bug: #1422383

commit_message:
processutils: execute(): fix option incompatibility

Issue: simultaneous usage of 'shell' and 'run_as_root' options led
to error.

Cause: it's actually a concealed TypeError: in 'shell'
mode the command argument is assumed to be a string, elsewhere
a list/tuple.

Fix: the command editing implied by 'run_as_root' is performed
with care taken of above tacit type assumption.

Change-Id: Iaba33e6fda67793ae2874ba278c990271ee5e47f
Closes-Bug: #1382873

commit_message:
Cleanup readme to offer more sane defaults

While the readme is just walking through an example dev/test setup,
it is still important to provide sane options here. This CR fixes
some items to make this more in line with current accepted defaults:

- Use AES128 instead of DES3 for key encryption
- Use example.com for all example domain names
- Make self signed root cert generation more clear
- Use a sane number of bits for RSA keys

Change-Id: I8d3730e1810cb0216f048960e437e8eff1f916f0

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-02-11 02:22:15.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/unit/common/test_ldap.py', 'keystone/common/ldap/core.py', 'keystone/tests/test_backend_ldap.py'], 'message': "Don't try to convert LDAP attributes to boolean

Currently, in the ldap2py function, attribute values are attempted

It attempts to convert an attribute to boolean first, then fallback

commit_message:
Don't try to convert LDAP attributes to boolean

Currently, in the ldap2py function, attribute values are attempted
to be converted to python friendly types.

It attempts to convert an attribute to boolean first, then fallback
as string. Any attribute value that is equal to 'TRUE' or 'FALSE'
are converted to boolean value.

Only 'enabled' attribute require this type of handling, and it is
already by enabled2py function. The additional handling on ldap2py
function should be removed.

Change-Id: Ifd1e91f98ae22a5e5f7b9b2ddbfddba156e16a6d
Closes-Bug: #1411478

The resize code in the driver is problematic. This stems
from the fact that a clone of the VM takes place. There are
a number of know issues with this:

2. resize may fail when a selected host does not have access

   1407050)

commit_message:
VMware: address instance resize problems

The resize code in the driver is problematic. This stems
from the fact that a clone of the VM takes place. There are
a number of know issues with this:
1. resize selects an invalid datastore (bug 1407438)
2. resize may fail when a selected host does not have access
   to the datastore that has the config driver file (bug
   1407050)
3. resized instances are not marked as owned by OpenStack on the
   VC (bug 1402784)

In fact we could do the resize on the existing VM. This has the
following advantages:
1. it does not need an additional VM
2. it fixes the bugs that are mentioned above
3. It is now far simpler and more robust
4. It does not require convoluted instance naming and tracking
5. VM deletion is simple
6. enables better test covergae

The patch makes use of the same VM for resizing.

Methods no longer used have been removed. These methods were
specific to the old resize.

Co-authored-by: Radoslav Gerganov <rgerganov@vmware.com>

Change-Id: Ibcb108c2e0f84a84c599d2e7762a11efc7659395
Closes-bug: #1407438
Closes-bug: #1407050
Closes-bug: #1402784

'}]
commit_message:
Allow symlinks in the container build

This patch permits symlinks in the docker build.  Normally docker
does not permit symlinked files in the build context sent to the
docker server.  To work around this problem, a secure directory
is created in /tmp and the container contents are copied to that
directory.  Any symlinks are turned into their non-symlinked
equivalents.

Change-Id: I38cd5aeed4c73b90449354a0979fc6ddf7891ccb
Implements-blueprint: linked-build

commit_message:
ofagent: Vendor code split

Install networking-ofagent from StackForge, using DevStack's
external plugins mechanism.

The following line needs to be added to the existing local.conf settings:
    enable_plugin networking-ofagent https://git.openstack.org/stackforge/networking-ofagent

Remove neutron_thirdparty/ryu, as Ryu is installed via
networking-ofagent's requirements.

Change-Id: I12287a47eac4689414f70b517ee37fb98b260e60
Partially-implements: blueprint core-vendor-decomposition
Partial-Bug: #1412653

This fixes the checks that Horizon does to ensure that the flavor a
user has chosen is big enough for the image they've chosen by

Closes-Bug: 1421017
Change-Id: I9c755c33d29886eeb5eedc48ddde7502fd234085

commit_message:
Fix flavor size checks and unit tests

This fixes the checks that Horizon does to ensure that the flavor a
user has chosen is big enough for the image they've chosen by
comparing the image virtual and on-disk sizes, as well as the
user-settable 'min_disk' image property.

This also fixes the unit tests for that functionality, which were
mostly broken.

Closes-Bug: 1421017
Change-Id: I9c755c33d29886eeb5eedc48ddde7502fd234085

commit_message:
Replace usage of LazyPluggable by stevedore driver

Stevedore lib support lazy loading, so this change replace
LazyPluggable class by stevedore extentions and remove it

Stevedore support usage of driver property since 0.4 release,
some of Openstack projects like glance is already using it.

Change-Id: I7d384a73861e18cac04e07f75abd60df7f183aa2

commit_message:
Remove nested service from DB API compute_nodes

Now all the calls to compute nodes are provided by ComputeNode object and
the service nested field is actually directly checking the Service object,
so we no longer need to add the service information in the DB API.
Also removed the no_date_fields option, as it was never in use.

Partially-Implements blueprint detach-service-from-computenode

Change-Id: I856cf1370824310f73292937df5403b9e77600bd

commit_message:
Initial support for Vertica Datastore in trove

Implemented:

1. CRUD operations on vertica DB using trove APIs.
2. User/Schema operations using Vertica Extensions.
3. Refactored extensions code to load datastore
   specific Extensions. Changes fully compatible to
   all implemented datastores.
4. Ignore Users are now per datastore config options.
5. Datastore-specific models are now better abstracted.
6. Unit tests to all methods for vertica.
7. Default Charset/Default Collation constants
   introduced to better abstract functional tests on
   different datastores.
8. Translations will be added after implementation of
   all functional parts of the BP.

Change-Id: Ib1a4933795f233f5f88a8564e319a6b648ca5274
Implements: blueprint vertica-db-support

commit_message:
Stack resources table improvement

In spite of the fact that status of stack resource is "Create complete",
the row color remains yellow instead of grey. This patch set keeps the
column for detailed states and adds a new hidden column for correct
states displaying.

Closes-Bug: #1385244

Change-Id: I2a9e5a6f456378dcd1f96d96f69fdba1527e4f25

commit_message:
Add missing stubs to project stacks tests

test_check_stack, test_suspend_stack and test_resume_stack all had
missing stubs for api.heat, causing weird logs in the tests, as well as
not testing the actions correctly as it would fail before reaching the
action code.

Change-Id: I6aeb2d2c1b6af9222e8ec3691b876051c638e3de
Partial-Bug: 1407981

commit_message:
Don't pass the port down to the floating ip processing

This is justified by the Law of Demeter.  I ran in to this while
trying to refactor the floating ip processing here [1].  The scope of
that patch can be reduced significantly with this refactor.  Also, it
helps us to decouple the floating ip NAT processing from the details
of the port which is a long-term goal.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/142863/

Change-Id: I606dfd43977934f1accea60911e10e71c1cbba73
Partially-Implements: bp/restructure-l3-agent

commit_message:
Support Manila pools in NetApp Clustered Data ONTAP driver

The Cinder pools feature is being ported to Manila, and drivers must be
updated to report pools in order to use this feature.  This patch adds
support for pools to the NetApp Clustered Data ONTAP driver for Manila.

Implements blueprint support-pools-in-netapp-cdot-driver

Change-Id: Iba327a745227e6219e6e1fc77af407f097905d8f

commit_message:
Allow adding to INSTALLED_APPS from local_settings.py

Defines a new option, ADD_INSTALLED_APPS, which gets prepended
to the beginning of INSTALLED_APPS.

Change-Id: I956835c3e18edee9e223a607005b47a5c5977687

commit_message:
Adds support for user created f5 prefix names and route domains

Added the ability for the user of the f5 config script to override
the default prefix of RPC. This is needed when multiple labs are
running on the same f5.

Added the ability for the user of the f5 config script to use route
domains on their f5. This is used for multiple labs using the same
f5 LB

commit_message:
Fix serialization of datetime objects

json.dumps needs a custom default function to handle the
case of serializing a datetime object with an embedded Utc
object.  This CR adds a generic method to allow anyone
needed to perform such special processing to include it
all in one place.

Change-Id: I84a31e38bf97d83a62108d8cb8f0466ed7fc7d03
Closes-Bug: 1420442

commit_message:
Remove ImportError handling in dynamic_inventory

The import of netaddr any yaml is done within a try/except block. If an
ImportError occurs an error message is printed and the script ignores
it. Ansible does not display the printed message and the script will
still fail, just later on.

This commit removes the exception handling so that if there is an
ImportError the script will fail straight away.

Change-Id: Iff935db62bde954ac4ff0b920409c18dd494bdff
Closes-Bug: #1420312

commit_message:
Image data remains in backend for deleted image

Trying to delete image created using task api (import-from) image gets
deleted from the database, but image data remains in the backend. Import
task does not update the location of the image and it remains None even
image becomes active. Location entry is not added in the database in
image_locations table.

Added location information to the image before saving the image in
the database.

SecurityImpact

Conflicts:
	glance/common/scripts/image_import/main.py

Change-Id: Ie389de6538a9b98dc51c7d781b81b3ab10b83842
Closes-Bug: #1420696
(cherry picked from commit 78b5b0a9575cd5e9c4543ec0e8fd6072af1f0ebb)

commit_message:
Setup br-tun in secure fail mode to avoid broadcast storms

When not creating br-tun in secure fail mode, there are chances to
get a broadcast storm from br-tun.

For example, this occurs when at least three nodes have the br-tun
OpenFlow rules reset in and a broadcast/multicast packet enters br-tun.

This can happen if:
  * openvswitch is restarted, until the agent reloads the Openflow rules.
  * during neutron-openvswitch-agent restart, br-tun is reset, and there
is a few seconds timeframe where tunnel endpoints are plugged and OF
rules are reset.

Secure fail mode doesn't forward traffic by default if no rule is hit.

Change-Id: Iba5ded14179156decb16dcd4b898c026660f9653
Closes-bug: #1421232

commit_message:
Remove RPC dependency to create FIP agent gw port

The Floatingip Agent Gateway port was initially
created when the agent requests one through an
RPC exchange.

We are seeing more failures in this area of the
code where there is delay in getting the agent
gateway port from the plugin through RPC.

Change-Id: Ieaa79c8bf2b1e03bc352f9252ce22286703e3715
Related-bug: #1415522

commit_message:
Change disk serial to re-use volume UUID

Disk devices need the serial defined in the domain xml. Instead of
generating one randomly, we can simply reuse the volume's UUID that
already existed.

Change-Id: Iabb8805e8cc1ef7528e0853093d3ba990444feb1
Closes-bug: #1412443

commit_message:
Fix rabbit driver use of ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3

The rabbit driver required that ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 is defined, but
not all Python implementations define it.

The code was changed so that the "sslv3" value is only allowed for
the "kombu_ssl_version" version if ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv3 is defined in
the Python standard library.

The title of the commit in master was:

 Remove the use of PROTOCOL_SSLv3

but this was changed since it didn't describe the actual change.

Closes-Bug: #1395095
Change-Id: I2c1977c3bfc1923bcb03744e909f2e70c7fdb14c
(cherry picked from commit 42f55a1dda96d4ceecf8cca5fba9cd723673f6e3)

Recently a new package fence-agents-all (version 4.0.7) has been added
to the OSCI yum repo. This package provides and obsoletes fence-agents
version <= 3.1.13. Due to a poor integration of puppet with package
management tools installing fence-agents with puppet fails:

Debug: Package[fence-agents](provider=yum): Ensuring => latest
Debug: Executing '/usr/bin/yum -d 0 -e 0 -y install fence-agents'
Debug: Executing '/bin/rpm -q fence-agents --nosignature --nodigest --qf %{NAME} %|EPOCH?{%{EPOCH}}:{0}| %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH} :DESC: %%{SUMMARY}\n'
Error: Could not update: Could not find package fence-agents

puppet does not try to figure out if fence-agents is provided by some
other package and query the status of that package, hence the error.
As a work around update the manifests to require fence-agents-all package.
A proper way to solve the problem is to fix dependencies of the packages
(if cobbler needs fence-agents it should depend on it so yum picks a proper
version of fence-agents without any tricks in manifests).

Closes-Bug: #1419889
Change-Id: I208e187def737d05d033e95f34ae5ca58ece9bd0
"}]
commit_message:
Fix nailgun and cobbler containers build failure.

Recently a new package fence-agents-all (version 4.0.7) has been added
to the OSCI yum repo. This package provides and obsoletes fence-agents
version <= 3.1.13. Due to a poor integration of puppet with package
management tools installing fence-agents with puppet fails:

Debug: Package[fence-agents](provider=yum): Ensuring => latest
Debug: Executing '/usr/bin/yum -d 0 -e 0 -y install fence-agents'
Debug: Executing '/bin/rpm -q fence-agents --nosignature --nodigest --qf %{NAME} %|EPOCH?{%{EPOCH}}:{0}| %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH} :DESC: %%{SUMMARY}\n'
Error: Could not update: Could not find package fence-agents

puppet does not try to figure out if fence-agents is provided by some
other package and query the status of that package, hence the error.
As a work around update the manifests to require fence-agents-all package.
A proper way to solve the problem is to fix dependencies of the packages
(if cobbler needs fence-agents it should depend on it so yum picks a proper
version of fence-agents without any tricks in manifests).

Closes-Bug: #1419889
Change-Id: I208e187def737d05d033e95f34ae5ca58ece9bd0

subject: Add horizon.cookies.getRaw to access raw cookie values
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-02-16 07:56:44.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/static/horizon/js/angular/horizon.js'], 'message': "Add horizon.cookies.getRaw to access raw cookie values

Since porting to ngCookie's $cookieStore, horizon.cookies supports
values of type object. In order to implement this, all values are
stored in their JSON representations. This however removes the ability
to read values set by the backend, since horizon.cookies.get attempts
to deserialize the cookie value assuming it is stored in JSON.

cookie values instead of modifying horizon.get to be more adaptive
to non-JSON values, because that would mean the statement
horizon.put('keyBackend', horizon.get('keyBackend')) yields unequal
before and after values when accessing cookies set by the backend.

commit_message:
Add horizon.cookies.getRaw to access raw cookie values

Since porting to ngCookie's $cookieStore, horizon.cookies supports
values of type object. In order to implement this, all values are
stored in their JSON representations. This however removes the ability
to read values set by the backend, since horizon.cookies.get attempts
to deserialize the cookie value assuming it is stored in JSON.

This change implements an additional utility method to access raw
cookie values instead of modifying horizon.get to be more adaptive
to non-JSON values, because that would mean the statement
horizon.put('keyBackend', horizon.get('keyBackend')) yields unequal
before and after values when accessing cookies set by the backend.
Moreover, horizon.cookies.getRaw helps developers to be more mindful
of accessing cookie values set outside of the Horizon frontend.

Change-Id: I21cd641b5495f57492a210ce88228f3e8783b86f
Closes-Bug: #1358911

commit_message:
Add get_current_env() to fix the decorator download_astute_yaml

 AttributeError: 'FuelWebClient' object has no attribute 'env'

Move class detection to the separate method and use it.

commit_message:
[wip] enable tempest scenarios for aio

This patch updates the tempest resources play to create all the
pre-requistes for running the commit_aio tempest tests.  This is
currently test_minimum_basic and test_swift_basic_ops.

Also defaults gate-check-commit RUN_TEMPEST and DEPLOY_TEMPEST variables
to yes.

The option to specify an endpoint type for Tempest is also added.

Closes-Bug: #1419094
Change-Id: Ib92b30f040cf05202d7785c8a3132150d31ef92e

commit_message:
fuel_upgrade: add retries for getting token

After starting a new Keystone container, the first attempt to get a token
fails. Unfortunately, the logs keep silent and say nothing. As a workaround,
we can just increase retries number.

Closes-Bug: #1403798

commit_message:
Handle SPBM SecurityError

SPBM APIs throw SecurityError on session expiry. Currently
it is unhandled which could result in session reconnection
failure. This patch fixes it.

commit_message:
Add support for updating a bay

Users can use these commands to add/remove/update bay attribute(s):
magnum bay-update <bay_id> replace <path=value>
magnum bay-update <bay_id> add <path=value>
magnum bay-update <bay_id> remove <path=value>

For example, this command updates the node_count attribute of a bay:
magnum bay-update 0aab40ba-3f48-4e6e-88a6-247be18b9711 replace node_count=1

Change-Id: If003beaca8e7e8bbdff2cf24d2810b0db9efdf41
Implements: blueprint update-node-count

commit_message:
Use plugin ids instead of versions to enable/disable plugin

With plugins patching feature we cannot rely on
plugin version and plugin name to find the correct
plugin, because version can be changed after minor
plugin update, e.g. 1.0.0 -> 1.0.1.

Add migrations to replace plugin versions with
plugin ids. And use new code to enable/disable
plugins.

Change-Id: I44b04893a3b061fa31ce7612f8172ed0a58b1acd
Implements: blueprint plugins-security-fixes-delivery

commit_message:
Revert "Fix shared firewall policy can not be displayed in horizon"

This reverts commit ca8df08bb8ed03981b7a0f9d6fedb3418b061804.

The reverted commit introduced a regression that all firewall
related resources from all projects are shown in the project panel
if a user has admin role. It violates the design policy of the
Project dashboard (which focuses on project-related resources).
A fix for the original bug 1294541 is coming in the subsequent patch.

Closes-Bug: #1422081
Related-Bug: #1294541
Change-Id: Ie8864b92b4ffb59681c0d18ac8b5f09f636d5fba

commit_message:
Move logging to use oslo_log library

The oslo-incubator log modlule has been removed, so port to the oslo_log
library.  Note this uses the new (non namespaced, e.g oslo.log) import
convention, we'll need to align other imports in a future commit.

Some import reordering was required due to pedantic H30[57] checks, and
the services have all been converted to initialize the oslo_log library
as this is done differently to the log.py in incubator.

Change-Id: Ib5a97123fe1b287bc531e42d7887c13ba6205628

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-02-17 07:30:45.000000000', 'files': ['glance/common/scripts/image_import/main.py', 'glance/tests/unit/common/scripts/image_import/test_main.py'], 'message': 'Image data remains in backend for deleted image

Trying to delete image created using task api (import-from) image gets
deleted from the database, but image data remains in the backend. Import

image becomes active. Location entry is not added in the database in

SecurityImpact

Change-Id: Ie389de6538a9b98dc51c7d781b81b3ab10b83842
Closes-Bug: #1420696
'}]
commit_message:
Image data remains in backend for deleted image

Trying to delete image created using task api (import-from) image gets
deleted from the database, but image data remains in the backend. Import
task does not update the location of the image and it remains None even
image becomes active. Location entry is not added in the database in
image_locations table.

Added location information to the image before saving the image in
the database.

SecurityImpact

Change-Id: Ie389de6538a9b98dc51c7d781b81b3ab10b83842

commit_message:
Quiesce boot from volume instances during live snapshot

With this patch, nova will automatically quiesce active volume boot
instances on creating volume snapshots by image-create command.
After volume snapshots are completed, the instance is unquiesced.

if the boot volume has 'os_require_quiesce=yes' image metadata,
the snapshotting is aborted when quiescing fails. Otherwise,
quiescing is skipped and the snapshotting is continued.

To utilize this feature in KVM instances, qemu-guest-agent must be
installed in the guest and the image metadata must have
'hw_qemu_guest_agent=yes' property.

Change-Id: Ic43dfa441fad8fefaa41b1db43ad19b15dc483c3
Implements: blueprint quiesced-image-snapshots-with-qemu-guest-agent

commit_message:
Remove the import of oslo_i18n lib in Juno

To address bug 1408099 I submitted a patch that
removed the calls to the private method in the i18n
code (change I2ae3d9b98c107cebaf386adbdcdb3cfafee070be).

Unfortunately as can be seen in the patch review,
my work was modified by another contributor and an update
of the oslo_18n lib which included a test fixture to togle
lazy translations was added.

This was probably fine for Master, HOWEVER that patch was
then back ported to Juno, which was completely inappropriate
as Juno was not using the oslo_i18n lib but using
openstack/common/gettextutils (change 894f20d).

This patch modifies the change that was submitted and removes the
import of the oslo_i18n lib which should have never been introduced
in stable in the first place.

Before somebody proposes it, leaving the lib dependency and capping
it is NOT the right answer here.  The lib should absolutely not be
introduced/back-ported in to stable.  Especially in this case where
it simply is used for a unit test that quite frankly is a crap test
that shouldn't be there to begin with.  There is no reason I can see
at all why we are testing translations in Cinder unit tests, that
should be left to the unit test for the library itself.

Change-Id: I5776d9f54d7a85d74311d9b8dbbe28fb81c62027
Closes-Bug: #1420335

commit_message:
Fixes total_capacity_gb value in CloudByte driver.

CloudByte storage returns total capacity value in two formats. One is
numeric and the other is alphanumeric.

Previously data['total_capacity_gb'] was referring the alphanumeric value
& now it is referring to the correct numeric value.

In addition, changes were made to test_cloudbyte.py to unit test
free_capacity_gb and total_capacity_gb.

Closes-Bug: 1420746

Change-Id: I601c2a78c1727bc815771ca26aea928fa2887d09

commit_message:
Refactoring task output: renaming 'output' to 'result' for task

* The reason behing this renaming is that task being an action/workflow
  invocation doesn't have input, it configures input for action/workflow.
  So to distinguish this difference and simplify communication around
  tasks it's been decided to rename 'task output' to 'task result'.
* Fixed required unit tests
* Removed weird transformation from 'output' to 'result' in task DB model
* Removed 'output' field in task REST resource, left only 'result'
  (it caused a lot of confusion before)
* Created a stub for data flow evaluate_effective_task_result() method
  that is supposed to calculate a final task result based on task
  invocations

Change-Id: I8c0e159c5c074185e0edc1982a01ad4f525b4d11

commit_message:
Refactoring task output: adding ActionInvocation model

* Added ActionInvocation DB model to represent one execution of
  task action/workflow. So Task and ActionInvocation are related
  as "one-to-many".
* Added unit tests
* Added custom LongText type that transforms to "LONGTEXT" in
  case of MySQL which has 2^32 bytes capacity.
* Minor refactoring and TODOs for the upcoming work

TODO:
* Write method for calculating effective task output in all cases:
  * Task doesn't have a retry policy and 'with-items'
  * Task has retry policy
  * Task has 'with-items'
  * Task has retry policy and 'with-items' together
* Refactor engine, workflow handlers and task controller to use
  action invocations and represent task result (output) in a new form

Change-Id: I612c523b32f9a4878401d4e848ea517234521c9f

subject: Prohibit stack check in suspend state
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-01-30 11:51:20.000000000', 'files': ['heat/tests/test_engine_service.py', 'heat/engine/service.py'], 'message': 'Prohibit stack check in suspend state

If stack is in suspend state it was possible to check the stack
in this state. However, there was no possibility to resume
or suspend stack again(only update, delete or create).
It simply fails because resources generate exceptions,
The patch prohibits check checking if stack is in suspend state.
In addition, added unit test for the case above.

Closes bug: #1415408

Change-Id: Ia49a997324afb17d6c18df0101ef8cbf10e8ebb5
'}]
commit_message:
Prohibit stack check in suspend state

If stack is in suspend state it was possible to check the stack
in this state. However, there was no possibility to resume
or suspend stack again(only update, delete or create).
It simply fails because resources generate exceptions,
The patch prohibits check checking if stack is in suspend state.
In addition, added unit test for the case above.

Closes bug: #1415408

Change-Id: Ia49a997324afb17d6c18df0101ef8cbf10e8ebb5

commit_message:
Add visibility filter to datastore versions

Allows datastore versions to be hidden from all users except those
explicitly allowed by their tenant. Implemented via a visibility
attribute for datastore versions (defaulting to 'public'), and a
datastore version member table for controlling access to non-public
datastore versions by tenant. Membership is controlled via a new set of
mgmt api calls.

Implements: blueprint datastore-visibility
DocImpact: visibility attr added to datastore_version show payload
Co-Authored-By: Riddhi Shah <ridhi.j.shah@gmail.com>
Change-Id: Ic8024a631530ba295688d7e49e895f50cb2f32ef

commit_message:
Add support for chiscsi iscsi helper

The chiscsi target works as a drop in replacement for IET/TGT with
minor configuration differences. This patch implements support for
this as the 'cxtadm' iscsi_helper.
Certification results :  https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1417499

DocImpact

Implements: blueprint chiscsi-iscsi-helper

Correct import order in qos_specs_manage.py

commit_message:
Use haproxy's http-server-close by default

At load, haproxy begins accumulating a large number of connections to
backend services stuck in TIME_WAIT state. Eventually, this leads to
stalled requests to OpenStack API services. http-server-close solves
that problem.

Change-Id: Ie405fe2d384d9d8375f60ad2c3c9885f41fe6d49
Closes-Bug: 1413104
(cherry picked from commit 6c6bfc35f779774141274579b948280518f57e2d)

commit_message:
Add a domain to federated users

Currently in the token returned from keystone, for a federated
user, the 'domain' section is missing. This was as designed, since
federated users do not exist in keystone. However this was caused
some issues with the upcoming non-persistent tokens, as well as
keystonemiddleware.

The solution should be to add a domain section, where we use a
reserved value of 'Federated', for both ID and name of the domain.

Change-Id: I4ad9fb55e8258e091ac78f628e5cb5b3add611a3
Implements bp federated-direct-user-mapping

commit_message:
Removal of uneeded guest mount_point from taskmgr

In an effort to promote a better seperation of concerns between
the taskmanager and the guest impls, the mount_point was identifed
as a field the taskmanager didnt actually use. By removing the
mount_point from the taskmanager, we are closer to being able to
provide a custom guest implmenentation without affecting the
existing impls and taskmanager. This is also an effort to better
define the contract between the guest and the taskmanager.

If the guestagent API detects that the user has provided a mount_point
argument, an error is issued. This sets us up to being able to rev the
API at some point and eliminate the argument. But, that's a matter for
another day.

Resubmitting with a manual rebase to kick out the Deprecated TroveCI

Closes-Bug: #1346881
Co-Authored-By: Michael Basnight <mbasnight@gmail.com>

Change-Id: If0f6f375aa74e6ac40a5ccefd0a6b2b0e7e04ab0

commit_message:
Set name on container returned by create_container

Since the underlying PUT to /containers doesn't return a new body, we're
not returning anything useful out of the object_store.create_container
proxy except for the headers that come back. Since we have the name, we
can set the name property on the object so it's actually useful to build
on. Right now you can't create a container and then build objects on it
since you lost the name.

The test in the change is because before we had the mock return itself,
which already had the name attribute set. Now we return a blank
Container and ensure that line 109 does its job in setting that name.

Change-Id: Iaab8595ec505cd90a18d71c5da4e066fd96661fb
Closes-Bug: 1422503

commit_message:
Adds backup/restore support for mongodb

Adds support to do full backups and restore mongodb single instance

Changes:

Added mongo_impl for backup and restore strategies
Updated backupagent.py to load backup_namespace and
        restore_namespace from config group section
Updated manager to invoke backup and restore
Updated common/cfg.py to load group attribs (backup_namespace,
                restore_namespace etc under [mongodb], [mysql]
Increased timeout for utils.execute() that execs mongorestore cmd

commit_message:
Removes '.' from GuestError exception message

Reasons:
- GuestError exception message is used to show an original_message
  and also adds a period '.' at end, but many-a-times, the
  original_message contains '.' at end, and the message gets to
  have '..' at end.

Changes:
- Removed the '.' from GuestError exception message.
- Added the '.' to the exception messages raised from volume.py,
  because it should be the responsibility to send '.'
  at end of message.

Change-Id: Ib1357f063f39b8544f341895bc164f33e69394fe
Closes-Bug: #1290925

commit_message:
Add instance ID validation stage while creating incremental backup

Reasons:
 - user is able to create incremental backup
   using parent backup taken from another instance.

Changes:
 - adding instance validation stage while
   attempting to create incremental backup;
 - unit/int tests proposed.

Behaviour:
 - when attempting to create incremental backup by using
   parent from different instance server side
   will raise ParentBackupIDMismatch exception;
 - from user perspective exception will be interpreted
   as HTTP Forbidden(403) according to RFC 2616 -- Trove server site
   understood the request, but is refusing to fulfill
   it due to IDs mismatch.

Change-Id: I1eef06c887e2e1acc3b101d4294b22c3470e6b87
Closes-Bug: #1344133

Closes-Bug: #1340163
"}]
commit_message:
Fix parent backup state validation

Reasons:
 - there's no parent backup checks at incremental
   backup creation step, so, users are allowed to
   attempt to create incremental backup with FAILED parent.

Changes:
 - adding validation step that checks parent backup
   state and raises exception if it's FAILED;
 - parent validation was moved to speed up failing
   if backup is FAILED;
 - unit/int tests proposed.

 Behaviour:
 - server will raise ParentBackupFailedError;
 - from user perspective error will be interpreted
   as HTTP Forbidden(403) according to RFC 2616.

Change-Id: I498026570bf8e91da9b5e0a71c66050d5521fe8d
Closes-Bug: #1340163

commit_message:
Fix replica source state validation

Reasons:
 - creating a slave for instance Trove
   doesn't validate that master exist,
 - replica source is not proper state.
   In this case trove-api needs to check
   if replica source is  ACTIVE and raise
   HTTP 422 UnprocessableEntity in cases when
   status is not ACTIVE

Changes:
 - adding validation step that checks if master exists and in proper state.

Change-Id: I731d75c1463fbcb4d9795756f9b38f7e8ae37c9c
Closes-Bug: #1357704

commit_message:
Make storage strategy available for trove API and TM

The storage strategy is only available for guestagent code.
This needs to be made available for API and taskmanager so
that it can access the storage to authenticate, copy or
delete backups. The bulk of the work is just moving the
storage strategy code from the guestagent package to the
trove common.

partially implements: blueprint cross-region-backup-availability

Change-Id: I4d806b5f5c61db489581cd78838fea178dbc113d

commit_message:
Get default configuration for version + flavor

This patch allows users to get the default config on a datastore version
flavor so they can know what the defaults are when creating a config
group that is not attached to an instance. This will help give a clear
description of what the config values are before making "custom" changes
to the config group.

Changes:
  - New API path which returns the default config for a specified
    datastore version and flavor

Change-Id: I306285916e5833b96aedf3b4909dece3a7d1aae1
Implements: blueprint default-config-values-for-datastore-version-flavor

commit_message:
Tests: Don't require binding to port 4444

If some other process is listening on port 4444,
test_server_pool_waitall will fail with:

RuntimeError: Could not bind to 127.0.0.1:4444 after
trying for 30 seconds

This test doesn't require use of this specific port,
so let it pick an unused port to avoid this failure.

Closes-Bug: #1421759

Change-Id: I7e6d6f574cd2bbb2fa067001bba4b09b5204a5e1

filters by tenant_id when some value is selected per resource
per tenant.

v2_0.Client now contains both base features of HTTP clients
and API methods which talk to Neutron server. We have so many
API methods now and it is not easy to find the base features
from the class.
This commit just split the base features into ClientBase.

Change-Id: I00b78569ad09efc59624ee73a6786d77226bda20
'}]
commit_message:
Split base function of v2_0.Client into a separate class

v2_0.Client now contains both base features of HTTP clients
and API methods which talk to Neutron server. We have so many
API methods now and it is not easy to find the base features
from the class.
This commit just split the base features into ClientBase.

Change-Id: I00b78569ad09efc59624ee73a6786d77226bda20

commit_message:
Use oslo.log instead of incubator

Most of changes are just replacing

from keystone.openstack.common import log
  with
from oslo_log import log

There are some other specific changes that had to be made
  * Initialize logger in keystone/config.py

Change-Id: I859edb71c434051ffe7f34c16018b738ddb71e3b

commit_message:
service-split should not add in entries from the *aas conf files

Submittion I16b5e5b2 [1] trys to read config entries out of
neutron-{service}.conf which will deprive the change for neutron
service projects to override config entries in their unit tests.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/151375/

Change-Id: I628598a6f7bdfcb69e8f55159eb1779e94471b48
Closes-Bug: #1420139

commit_message:
Add 'type' parameter to compute image schema

Compute image API returns a response which includes 'type' parameter,
but the parameter was not defined in the response schema.
This patch adds it.

Change-Id: I3eee9783da51084200e188ab0c25c7ae7433831e

commit_message:
Allow Json patch to take an integer value

This commit allows clients to send a Json patch with integer value, which is
necessary for modifying an integer field (i.e. node_count) of a controller.

Partially implements: blueprint update-node-count

This removes several things from the public namespace of base.py, which are
internal implementation details. It also changes the special name used to store

commit_message:
Remove internal items from public namespace

This removes several things from the public namespace of base.py, which are
internal implementation details. It also changes the special name used to store
an actual attribute from just _$name to _obj_$name to avoid obvious and simple
collisions. We use "obj_" in a lot of places for things built into the base
object, so that seems appropriate.

Change-Id: Ic6f4f0e0e71c1d8574292eb44aa925dfbf329d8b

commit_message:
Fixes error message during volume snapshot creation

When a user who is close to his quota tries to create a volume snapshot,
he sees the error message "Unable to create volume snapshot" which does
not provide any details about the real error. This patch will show a
detailed error message to the user.

Change-Id: I9b4af3f9bf5a9bc65c677e664668d0c2c1a3a3d5
Closes-Bug: #1421317

This change adds a new script, configure_for_func_testing.sh, that
automates configuration of a host to support functional testing.  The
script's functionality is consumed by a refactored version of
gate_hook.sh, and both minimizes runtime and removes the previous
dependency on the devstack-gate repo.

Additionally, the dsvm-functional tox env is no longer dependent on
devstack to deploy neutron's rootwrap configuration system-wide.

Change-Id: Iaf43be458bdf3c4535f95ee5a3a3b47a744020a0
"}]
commit_message:
Automate host configuration for functional testing

This change adds a new script, configure_for_func_testing.sh, that
automates configuration of a host to support functional testing.  The
script's functionality is consumed by a refactored version of
gate_hook.sh, and both minimizes runtime and removes the previous
dependency on the devstack-gate repo.

Additionally, the dsvm-functional tox env is no longer dependent on
devstack to deploy neutron's rootwrap configuration system-wide.
Rootwrap configuration is now deployed to the target tox venv on each
tox invocation.

Change-Id: Iaf43be458bdf3c4535f95ee5a3a3b47a744020a0

commit_message:
Add support for PCI ports in OS::Neutron::Port

With the introduction of PCI Passthrough SR-IOV support in Neutron and Nova,
users can create PCI passthough ports.
This spec propose to add modify the resource type OS::Neutron::Port
to support PCI passthough ports.

Change-Id: I664356730cdcea2d43a27dae3fc1cc0d5ef56215

commit_message:
Make auto console type in network topology work

The "open console" link in "Network Topology" does not autodetect
console type. This can be reproduced by setting CONSOLE_TYPE="AUTO" (or
ommiting the setting as AUTO is default value) while using SPICE
console.

Autodetection is correctly implemented in Instances view
(openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/instances/console.py), but in
network topology
(openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/network_topology/views.py in
JSONView) is only simple check, that ignore "RDP" and "AUTO".

Refactor get_console method, to return a tuple of console type and
console url, so other places can also use the method.

Change-Id: I064db5f1e5d363c9e6736703b66e78ad4e3de4d0
Closes-bug: #1403922

commit_message:
V2 API Refactoring

The V2 API are really monolithic and difficult to maintain.

This patch separates the various controller code in separte files
simplifying the overall structure and making the code more readable.

Moreover, this should simplify the integration/substitution of API
that now can be clearly stated in the v2 file injecting a controller
from a new source.

Change-Id: I0127ae33b1e0db525ce9b58e9e8c5f15f5fe1ae3

subject: Remove Sample data from Resource metadata field
revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2014-07-31 17:02:27.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometer/tests/storage/test_storage_scenarios.py', 'ceilometer/storage/impl_sqlalchemy.py'], 'message': "Remove Sample data from Resource metadata field

    Before fix a Resource was created with an un-
    predictable set of Sample data in the
    Resource's metadata field.

    This information did not make sense to be in
    this place for the following reasons:

    There can be multiple Samples related to any
    resource

    There is no way to predict what Sample data
    will be returned (other than the latest)

    The metadata field is a free-form
    field for filtering, not for primary
    instance data.

    This fix will remove the sample data values
    from metadata.  The result will be that the
    field will no longer contain unpredictable
    data values and will be truer to its
    function as a free-form user-defined field.

    Added test changes.

Closes-Bug: #1348651

Change-Id: I8dbf6d7a6c238aa3085e5b2d0b9249b00eb2d526
"}]
commit_message:
Remove Sample data from Resource metadata field

    Before fix a Resource was created with an un-
    predictable set of Sample data in the
    Resource's metadata field.

    This information did not make sense to be in
    this place for the following reasons:

    There can be multiple Samples related to any
    resource

    There is no way to predict what Sample data
    will be returned (other than the latest)

    The metadata field is a free-form
    field for filtering, not for primary
    instance data.

    This fix will remove the sample data values
    from metadata.  The result will be that the
    field will no longer contain unpredictable
    data values and will be truer to its
    function as a free-form user-defined field.

    Added test changes.

Closes-Bug: #1348651

Change-Id: I8dbf6d7a6c238aa3085e5b2d0b9249b00eb2d526

commit_message:
ML2: Hierarchical port binding

The ML2 port binding logic is modified to support hierarchical
bindings. If a mechanism driver's bind_port() calls continue_binding()
rather than set_binding(), the supplied dynamic segments are used for
another level of binding.

Gerrit Spec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/139886/

Implements: blueprint ml2-hierarchical-port-binding

Change-Id: Id741c2d6c443fa0eac5ecf8d964b3fc14b5d3abe

commit_message:
let the date field include µS

The apache error logs formatted by keystone go to µS instead of
mS. Because of which the parser doesn't work on keystone
logs. Normalizing the apache logs might be possible, however allowing
this to work in the mean time seems reasonable.

Change-Id: I7627c52d492de2dcba524c6da3bed69f94820932

commit_message:
ML2: DB changes for hierarchical port binding

To support hierarchical port binding, the driver and segment columns
are moved from the ml2_port_bindings and ml2_dvr_port_bindings tables
to a new ml2_port_binding_levels table. This new table can store
multiple levels of binding information for each port. It has the host
as part of its primary key so that it can be used for both normal and
DVR port bindings.

The cap_port_filter column is also removed from the
ml2_dvr_port_bindings table, since the adjacent driver and segment
columns are being moved, and this can trivially be done via the same
DB migration. It was included in the table by mistake and was never
used.

The logic required for hierarchical port binding will be implemented
in a dependent patch.

Gerrit Spec: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/139886/

Partially-implements: blueprint ml2-hierarchical-port-binding

Change-Id: I08ddc384763087fbac0fa3da3ed6e99b897df031

It seems Guest Agents are active before making sure that it can

Add a rpc connection checker while setting up guest agent. Make
 sure it can connected to amqp service before it define itself

Closes-Bug: #1248322
"}]
commit_message:
Guest Agent goes active before connecting to message queue

It seems Guest Agents are active before making sure that it can
 connect to amqp server. Clients who try to make API calls that
 require the Guest Agent, such as listing the databases for an
 instance result in HTTP errors.

Add a rpc connection checker while setting up guest agent. Make
 sure it can connected to amqp service before it define itself
 to Active status. An error will raise if rpc connection failed.
 Add rpc connection checker at the setup step will remain all API
 focus on handling database operations. After rpc is checked client
 won't need to worry any AMQP error occur while sending API action
 when Guest go ACTIVE.

Change-Id: I90e9c33d683a3ee23e66ad48eb402c8bb1ab3fca
Closes-Bug: #1248322

commit_message:
XenAPI: Move some boot-time functions to install-time

The boot-time script (prepare_guest.sh) is one of the less reliable parts
of the install process.  This change enables SSH into the host as well as
reporting of the IP address.  This significantly helps debugging issues
now and enables moving of all other setup code to being executed over SSH.

Change-Id: I1555f1d91353ba8b75e2de4607df33ee20307a6e

commit_message:
Remove duplicated resource when pollster polling

Different resource discovery probably leads duplicated resources for
pollster, thus duplicated samples with side effect. This patch removes
duplicated resources before polling, sends warning for the 1st time.

Closes-bug: #1418834

commit_message:
Moving policy engine implementation

This is the first step in moving the policy engine to
django_openstack_auth. It makes the policy check method pluggable
in openstack_dashboard as it is in horizon. To do this, the wrapper
around the policy engine is moved to a new file isolated from the
policy check method. A thin check method is left in policy.py to
allow the code and policy mix-ins to behave as now. The existing
policy test file is also moved for relocation. A new test file has
been added to exercise the simpler check method.

Once the actual engine is moved to django_openstack_auth, we'll be
able to remove policy_backend.py and the test version of
policy_backend.py as well.

Partially Implemenents: blueprint move-policy-engine

Change-Id: I591bcbe69bf255f1aa0346fdf869fac86d2e6d3d

commit_message:
libvirt: stub VIR_CONNECT_LIST_DOMAINS_ACTIVE for older libvirts

Depending on the version of libvirt, `VIR_CONNECT_LIST_DOMAINS_ACTIVE`
may not exist, so we need to stub out the attribute if it doesn't
exist using the create=True kwarg in mock.

This is added for test_list_instance_domains_fallback and we also
remove the skip in test_list_instance_domains_fast to use the stub.

Partial-Bug: #1422385

Co-authored-by: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: Id68801909a5561c2740e12de3238319fc4ea6338

subject: Log missing dir message only once
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-02-15 22:10:19.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_policy/policy.py', 'oslo_policy/tests/test_policy.py'], 'message': 'Log missing dir message only once

Some services that use the policy code create new Enforcers
frequently.  This means that if the policy_dirs are not found a
log message is emitted each time, which results in an excessive
amount of noise in the logs.  Instead, we only want to log the
missing dirs warning once per missing path.

While there is still some discussion going on over the proper way
to handle this, I would like to merge this simple fix so we can
backport it to the incubator code and fix the log spamming that is
currently a problem in some of the services.

Change-Id: I7b771b1df1bf0ad7ef69749856b44c92c5f36ffc
Closes-Bug: 1421863
'}]
commit_message:
Log missing dir message only once

Some services that use the policy code create new Enforcers
frequently.  This means that if the policy_dirs are not found a
log message is emitted each time, which results in an excessive
amount of noise in the logs.  Instead, we only want to log the
missing dirs warning once per missing path.

While there is still some discussion going on over the proper way
to handle this, I would like to merge this simple fix so we can
backport it to the incubator code and fix the log spamming that is
currently a problem in some of the services.

Change-Id: I7b771b1df1bf0ad7ef69749856b44c92c5f36ffc
Closes-Bug: 1421863

commit_message:
Log missing dir message only once

Some services that use the policy code create new Enforcers
frequently.  This means that if the policy_dirs are not found a
log message is emitted each time, which results in an excessive
amount of noise in the logs.  Instead, we only want to log the
missing dirs warning once per missing path.

Change-Id: I6d4dcdf7e61d8bbb7084068c7288077cb2e1d193
Closes-Bug: 1421863

commit_message:
Add code to generate a CSR in the stored key case

This code gets the private key referred to in the container_ref
and uses it to generate a CSR.  We assume that the required parameters
are present in the request because of validations previously performed
when the request was submitted.

Change-Id: I45f55b21e179d401a38db68201e8fb7202ffbf18
Implments: blueprint certificate-order-api

commit_message:
Make identity id mapping handle unicode

Identity id mapping is used to create public ids for local entities,
typically stored in LDAP backends. Part of the mapping involves
creating a hash of the local identifiers - but this hashing did
not correctly handle unicode. This patch fixes this.

(cherry picked from commit 4f0107e43491ec5ed829b83eae7be32fea5ba659)
Closes-Bug: 1419187

Change-Id: Icc2a6bc4a7e88004bbe6f86d3a96cff07be4c6f9
